Responsibilities:

Responsible for system administration of AD, VMware, Veeam Backup, monitoring of firewalls, switches, VPN, Internet connectivity, and 2nd level desktop support;
Implementing system configurations with monitoring, DR, and backup solutions with IT policies with aspects of IT infrastructure;
Perform routine database administration and maintenance tasks for Application systems;
Provide technical advice as required for procurement or other projects;
Supervise vendors to perform infra upgrade;
Continuously improve effectiveness of security risk control and review IT security risks; and
Prepare and maintain system management and computer operation documentations

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in Computer Engineering / Information Technology or related discipline;
At least 5 years’ solid experience in server administration and networking;
Solid experience of Windows Server platform, Active Directory, Group Policy, VMware, Networking, Firewall;
Holder of certificate of CCNA or MCSE would be an advantage;
Knowledge on cloud infrastructure;
Able to work independently and under pressure; and
Proficient in spoken and written English and Chinese

Working hours: 5-day work (must include Saturday)

Benefits: End of Year Payment, Annual Leave, Birthday Leave, Bank Holidays, Education Allowance, Medical & Dental Insurance, Free Shuttle Bus (Kowloon / Tuen Mun / Tin Shui Wai)



We offer competitive remuneration package for suitable candidates. For interested parties, please send your resume with professional qualifications and expected salary to Human Resources Department by clicking “Apply Now”. 

Applicants not invited for interview within 6 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. Unsuccessful applications will be kept for 12 months and then destroyed. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Responsibilities: 

Work closely with other departments to follow up repacking processes;
Liaise with customers and service providers to ensure smooth operation;
Follow up invoice billing, chasing outstanding payment;
Prepare regular inventory reports and analysis;
Responsible for salary and overtime payment calculation;
Ad-hoc tasks or projects as assigned.

 Requirements: 

Diploma holder in Business Administration, Logistics or related discipline;
At least 5 years’ relevant experience, preferred in logistics industry;
Strong communication skills with good command of both spoken and written English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Mature, initiative, willing to learn & able to work independently;
Proficiency in MS Office application, including Chinese word processing;
Working location will be Lau Fau Shan;
Immediately available is highly preferred.

 We offer competitive salary to the successful candidate. Interested candidates please send by mail or email your resume together with salary expectation to click "Apply Now".

Human Resources Department, DCH Logistics Company Limited
67-73 Fuk Hi Street, Yuen Long Industrial Estate, Yuen Long, New Territories.


