Responsibilities:
Review and approve credit applications of credit applications within the delegated approval authority; and provide recommendations for requiring higher approval authority;

Manage and monitor portfolio of assigned units and ensure credit quality and full compliance with Bank’s credit policies and risk appetites;

Highlight and identify exceptions against the Bank’s lending policies, standard terms and conditions being offered to borrowing clients; and

Perform other ad hoc projects or assignments.

Requirements:
University graduate in Risk Management, Finance, Accountancy, Business Administration or related disciplines;

CFA, Accountant and/or FRM is a plus; and HKIB ECF-CRM;

5-10 years’ solid experience of large corporate, FIG, SME, and/ or relationship management,

Sound knowledge in various corporate lending products, accounting principles and financial statement analysis;

Good understanding in key market and industry dynamics; and

Excellent analytical and quantitative skills with good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese including Putonghua.

Interested candidates, please click APPLY NOW  to apply.

