Major Responsibilities:   

This incumbent will be reporting to the Air Operations Manager and the prime responsibilities will include but not limited to :

Handle full set of Air Export documentation and operation.
Oversee the air export documentation, cargo planning, and other operational related tasks;
Liaise and build strong relationships with airlines, co-loaders and warehouses;
Communicate with CS and sales teams to attain a smooth operations process;
Ensure shipments and documentation are handed over to terminal timely and accurately;
Ensure pre-alert are sent to overseas offices and agents timely;
Responsible for customers’ enquiries and its correspondence;
Responsible for SOA mapping and credit control on monthly basis;

 Desired Skills and Experience:

F.5 / DSE or above;  
3-5 years’ air export experience in freight forwarding industry;  
Responsible, independent and strong personal motivation;
Proficient in PC skills and MS Office;  
Required to work on shift (Day / Noon / Night shift duty) and Alternate Saturday (9am to 6pm) – Roster to be assigned by the Manager;

The incumbent will be responsible for handling customers’ enquires, following up the delivery orders, stock inventory and providing clerical support in Operation.

The ideal candidate should be:

Form 5 or above;
At least 2 years’ relevant experience, preferred in logistics industry;
Proficiency in MS Office application, including Chinese word processing;
Good communication skills, willing to learn & able to work independently;
Working location will be Yuen Long Lau Fau Shan
Immediately available is highly preferred.



 We offer competitive salary, monthly incentive, medical insurance, life and personal accident insurance, annual leave and staff purchase discount to the successful candidate.  

We are equal opportunities employer. Applicants who are not invited within 2 months may consider their application unsuccessful. All applicants may be considered for other suitable positions with DCH Group / CITIC Pacific Group and will be deleted from our files after 6 months from the date of application.

Responsibilities:


Order process and upload PO into MIS system;
Follow up and ensure shipping schedule to meet the department target;
Prepare full set of order processing and shipment report;
Assist buying team on order status and coordinate with the sales team on the delivery requests;
Communicate with the internal department for arranging order instruction/payment request form and coordinating with the overseas vendors for the shipment schedule;
Monitor the order processing with the operation and ensure shipment on schedule;
Establish a good leadership with the internal team and well relationship with the internal department for the day to day operation and reporting
Review operation regularly and recommend improvement and action plan
Supervise team members to support daily distribution/operations.

Requirements: 


Bachelor Degree/ High Diploma in Logistics, Supply Chain Management, or a related disciplines;
Minimum 3 years experience in order processing field;
Energetic, motivated, full of initiative, shipping and logistics' knowledge is required and able to work independently and under pressure;

Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (e.g. Excel is a must);
Good command of interpersonal and communication skills;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Logistics Supervisor. 
We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.  Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date available

